09/09/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A Bosnian Serb accused of genocide committed against Bosniaks in Srebrenica in 1995 pleaded guilty in court on Wednesday (September 8th). Vlastimir Goljan admitted his involvement in the killing of more than 800 men and boys in the enclave. Three other people accused of the same crimes pleaded not guilty. (RTRS, Srna, Radio Free Europe - 08/09/10)
